The {{nihongo|'''Kajiyama Kofun'''|梶山古墳||}} is a [[Kofun period]] [[kofun|Kofun]] located in the Okamasu, Kokufucho, neighborhood of the city of {{ill|Tottori (city)|en|Tottori (city)|qid=Q200731|lt=Tottori|1=Tottori (city)}}, {{ill|Tottori Prefecture|en|Tottori Prefecture|qid=Q133935|lt=Tottori Prefecture|1=Tottori Prefecture}} in the {{ill|San&#39;in region|en|San&#39;in region|qid=Q398310|lt=San&#39;in region|1=San'in region}} of {{ill|Japan|en|Japan|qid=Q17|lt=Japan|1=Japan}}. The tumulus was designated a [[Monuments of Japan|National Historic Site of Japan]] in 1979. <ref name= "Bunka1">{{cite web |url= https://bunka.nii.ac.jp/db/heritages/detail/161988|title= 梶山古墳|trans-title= Kajiyama Kofun|language=Japanese |publisher=[[Agency for Cultural Affairs]] |accessdate=January 1, 2023}}</ref>
